        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 30 at 3:47PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 347 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Pittsboro, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Raleigh, Durham, Cary, Sanford, Pittsboro, Garner, Fuquay-Varina,
Angier, Goldston, and RDU International.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 800 PM EDT for central North
Carolina.</instruction>
